div.p: When loading the initial particles of a Simulation, it's possible that the configuration specifies a "subsimulation" to be executed and then copied in.
All those simulations happens during the initial loading process.

p.span: Interceptors are used to perform actions during the simulation loop. They are mostly used to extract and save data (Frames, Distributions, Profiles...) but can also be used to influence the Simulation (e.g. Thermostats ...).

div.p: Each Interceptors has a "frequency" which specifies how often it's executed.

div.p: A numerical integration scheme performs this task.
